+# Unknown Omission Ledger
+
+Pass: `unknown-omission-pass`
+Context: `bootstrap`
+Date: `2026-04-16`
+Model/provider/account: `gpt-5.4` / `native-codex` / `native-codex-session`
+Caveman used: `no`
+Live verification performed in this pass: `no`
+
+## Environment Drift Check
+
+- Prompt routing assumptions matched current route posture: `audit-map/29-status/route-health-native-codex.status` still shows native Codex clear for immediate execution.
+- The audit OS had stale wrapper truth for this specific pass: `audit-map/29-status/audit-air-mentor-ui-bootstrap-unknown-omission-pass.status` and `audit-map/30-checkpoints/audit-air-mentor-ui-bootstrap-unknown-omission-pass.checkpoint` still report `state=running` / `last_event=running` from `2026-04-15T22:18:16Z`, while `audit-map/25-accounts-routing/manual-action-required.md` records an overnight stop/failure for the same pass family and no terminal last-message artifact exists. This pass used direct file + repo truth and records that drift in durable memory.
+
+## Method
+
+1. Read the required bootstrap, coverage, memory, reconciliation, runbook, prompt-template, routing, status, checkpoint, queue, final-map, live-behavior, ML, UX, frontend-microinteraction, backend-provenance, workflow-automation, and validation artifacts.
+2. Cross-checked repo reality for:
+   - `src/`, `src/pages/`, `src/api/`
+   - `air-mentor-api/src/`, `air-mentor-api/src/db/`
+   - `scripts/`, `air-mentor-api/scripts/`
+   - `tests/`, `air-mentor-api/tests/`
+   - `.github/workflows/`
+3. Compared those inventories against `coverage-ledger.md`, `review-status-by-path.md`, `unreviewed-surface-list.md`, `15-final-maps/*`, and pass outputs.
+4. Ran an audit-map mention-count sweep outside inventory/status/artifact buckets to find code, script, and test surfaces that exist in repo reality but are missing or only thinly represented in durable maps.
+5. Opened candidate files directly before recording omissions.
+
+## New Omission Findings
+
+| ID | Path or subsystem | Omission type | Why current audit representation is insufficient | Evidence anchors | Closure action |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| UO-001 | Frontend/backend telemetry and startup-diagnostics family | Missing dependency/data-flow/runtime family | Current final maps and coverage notes discuss live session/CORS and startup API origin posture, but they do not represent the implemented telemetry path: frontend event emission and sink resolution, production-like startup diagnostics, backend relay acceptance, persisted operational event storage, or their dedicated tests. This is a real product/runtime surface, not just a utility. | `src/telemetry.ts`, `src/startup-diagnostics.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/modules/client-telemetry.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/lib/telemetry.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/lib/operational-event-store.ts`, `tests/frontend-telemetry.test.ts`, `tests/frontend-startup-diagnostics.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/client-telemetry.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/telemetry.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/telemetry-sink.test.ts` | Add a dedicated telemetry/startup-diagnostics overlay in dependency/data-flow/live maps; then verify live sink/config posture during `live-behavior-pass`. |
+| UO-002 | Sysadmin scoped hierarchy, provisioning, calendar, queue, and session helper cluster | Missing component-level frontend microinteraction coverage | The current frontend microinteraction map covers the broad sysadmin shell, request workspace, proof dashboard, and hierarchy restore, but it does not decompose section-scope encoding, scoped registry launches, bulk mentor assignment preview/apply, faculty-calendar/timetable editing, queue-dismiss key semantics, or the system-admin session boundary UX. These helpers materially change what a sysadmin can launch, save, preview, or recover. | `src/admin-section-scope.ts`, `src/system-admin-provisioning-helpers.ts`, `src/system-admin-scoped-registry-launches.tsx`, `src/system-admin-faculty-calendar-workspace.tsx`, `src/system-admin-timetable-editor.tsx`, `src/system-admin-session-shell.tsx`, `src/system-admin-action-queue.ts`, `src/system-admin-overview-helpers.ts`, `tests/system-admin-action-queue.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/admin-hierarchy.test.ts` | Extend `frontend-microinteraction-pass` with a sysadmin helper-cluster continuation focused on section scope, mentor bulk apply, calendar/timetable, and auth boundary behavior. |
+| UO-003 | Active-run, authoritative-first, live-run seeding, section-risk, and provisioning backend helper family | Missing backend provenance/parity semantics | Backend provenance already covers queue lineage at a high level, but it does not explicitly map the helpers that decide active-run recency, authoritative-vs-runtime fallback, live-run seeding from current operational data, dashboard diagnostics aggregation, section-risk aggregation, and mentor provisioning eligibility. These helpers are directly relevant to the already known concerns about active-run/checkpoint/semester coherence and same-truth parity. | `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-active-run.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-live-run-service.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-dashboard-service.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-section-risk-service.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-authoritative-first.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/lib/academic-provisioning.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/proof-run-queue.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/admin-hierarchy.test.ts` | Run a backend-provenance continuation that traces these helper services into role surfaces, same-student parity expectations, and live-proof lifecycle claims. |
+| UO-004 | Same-student parity seed generation pipeline | Missing script-behavior + parity-fixture lineage | The uncovered list already calls out same-student cross-surface parity as a high-risk gap, but the audit had not recorded that there is a dedicated fixture generator for parity-style data. Without mapping this script, the current audit misses how local parity scenarios are seeded and what truths they intend to stabilize. | `air-mentor-api/scripts/generate-academic-parity-seed.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/academic-parity.test.ts`, `tests/student-shell.test.tsx`, `tests/risk-explorer.test.tsx`, `tests/hod-pages.test.ts`, `tests/system-admin-proof-dashboard-workspace.test.tsx` | Add this generator and its consumers to `script-behavior-pass`, then feed that output into `same-student-cross-surface-parity-pass`. |
+| UO-005 | Live auth, password-probing, artifact snapshot, and Railway recovery helper chain | Missing script-behavior/live-recovery coverage | The workflow map names the top-level live scripts, but the internal helper chain that resolves credentials, probes teaching passwords, snapshots closeout evidence, and performs Railway recovery is currently unmapped. That helper chain affects how live verification recovers from drift and how evidence is bundled after verification. | `scripts/system-admin-live-auth.mjs`, `scripts/teaching-password-resolution.mjs`, `scripts/snapshot-final-closeout-artifacts.mjs`, `scripts/railway-recovery-chain.sh`, `scripts/verify-final-closeout-live.sh`, `.github/workflows/verify-live-closeout.yml`, `.github/workflows/deploy-railway-api.yml` | Cover these helpers in `script-behavior-pass`; link the results back into `live-behavior-pass` and deployment runbooks. |
+| UO-006 | Contract and observability test families | Missing test-evidence representation | Several contract suites exist, but current coverage narratives do not cite them: OpenAPI route-surface snapshotting, config/cookie posture, frontend startup diagnostics, backend/client telemetry relay, admin hierarchy, and queue-worker stop semantics. Their absence makes the current test posture look narrower than repo reality. | `tests/frontend-startup-diagnostics.test.ts`, `tests/frontend-telemetry.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/openapi.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/config.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/client-telemetry.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/telemetry.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/telemetry-sink.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/admin-hierarchy.test.ts`, `air-mentor-api/tests/proof-run-queue.test.ts` | Expand `test-gap-pass` or add a validation overlay so these suites are classified as proven evidence, not invisible coverage. |
+
+## Negative Checks
+
+- `.github/workflows/*` did not produce a genuinely new omission family in this pass. The current workflow map already covers all five workflow files at execution-system depth; the remaining workflow risks are the previously recorded live/local ambiguity and conditional-skip gaps.
+- `src/pages/*` route families remain materially represented. The new frontend omissions came from helper and shell files around sysadmin scope, telemetry, and restore behavior rather than from an entirely unmapped page module.
+
+## Audit OS Corrections Made During This Pass
+
+- `audit-map/01-inventory/component-index.md` was corrected to include `src/academic-workspace-route-helpers.ts`, `src/academic-workspace-route-surface.tsx`, and `src/telemetry.ts`, which had been omitted from the frontend inventory despite being active repo surfaces.
+
+## Pass Output Contract
+
+- Covered: bootstrap audit OS corpus, current status/checkpoint truth, repo inventories for frontend/backend/scripts/tests/workflows, and direct code/test/script samples for newly suspected omission families.
+- Files updated: `audit-map/01-inventory/component-index.md`, `audit-map/23-coverage/unreviewed-surface-list.md`, `audit-map/23-coverage/review-status-by-path.md`, `audit-map/23-coverage/coverage-ledger.md`, `audit-map/24-agent-memory/known-ambiguities.md`, `audit-map/24-agent-memory/working-knowledge.md`, `audit-map/14-reconciliation/reconciliation-log.md`, `audit-map/32-reports/unknown-omission-ledger.md`.
+- Remains uncovered: telemetry/startup-diagnostics flow mapping, sysadmin helper-cluster microinteractions, active-run/helper backend semantics, parity seed lineage, live helper-script behavior, and contract-suite incorporation into the test posture.
+- Contradictions or drift found: stale wrapper state for the previous `unknown-omission-pass` run versus later manual-action notes.
+- Routing/provider/account changed: no.
+- Caveman used: no.
+- Live verification performed: no.
+- Next pass: `script-behavior-pass`, then `frontend-microinteraction-pass` continuation, then `backend-provenance-pass` continuation, then `same-student-cross-surface-parity-pass`.
+- Manual checkpoint required: no, but the stale `unknown-omission-pass` wrapper state should be superseded before any queue-driven resume relies on it.

