 - The detached tmux control surface is inconsistent from this shell: `tmux ls` is visible, but `tmux has-session` can still return `Operation not permitted`, so some wrapper-driven stop/status operations may fail even when sessions exist.
-- The active `unattended-run-pass` currently has a non-terminal drift condition: after native quota failure and Arctic failover, status and checkpoint files still show `state=running` / `last_event=runtime-failure` with stale progress timestamps, so completion versus stall cannot yet be concluded from artifact truth alone.
